#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="sn3.14"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn3.14:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 3 "
msgstr "Linked Discourses 3 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn3.14:0.2"
msgid "2. Dutiyavagga "
msgstr "2. Childless "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
msgctxt "sn3.14:0.3"
msgid "14. Paṭhamasaṅgāmasutta "
msgstr "14. Battle (1st) "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: pts1ed1.83, pts2ed1.188, sc1
msgctxt "sn3.14:1.1"
msgid "Sāvatthinidānaṃ. "
msgstr "At Sāvatthī. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn3.14:1.2"
msgid "Atha kho rājā māgadho ajātasattu vedehiputto caturaṅginiṃ senaṃ sannayhitvā rājānaṃ pasenadiṃ kosalaṃ abbhuyyāsi yena kāsi. "
msgstr "Then King Ajātasattu Vedehiputta of Magadha mobilized an army of four divisions and marched to Kāsi to attack King Pasenadi of Kosala. "

msgctxt "sn3.14:1.3"
msgid "Assosi kho rājā pasenadi kosalo: "
msgstr "When King Pasenadi heard of this, "

msgctxt "sn3.14:1.4"
msgid "“rājā kira māgadho ajātasattu vedehiputto caturaṅginiṃ senaṃ sannayhitvā mamaṃ abbhuyyāto yena kāsī”ti. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn3.14:1.5"
msgid "Atha kho rājā pasenadi kosalo caturaṅginiṃ senaṃ sannayhitvā rājānaṃ māgadhaṃ ajātasattuṃ vedehiputtaṃ paccuyyāsi yena kāsi. "
msgstr "he mobilized an army of four divisions and marched to Kāsi to defend it against Ajātasattu. "

msgctxt "sn3.14:1.6"
msgid "Atha kho rājā ca māgadho ajātasattu vedehiputto rājā ca pasenadi kosalo saṅgāmesuṃ. "
msgstr "Then the two kings met in battle. "

msgctxt "sn3.14:1.7"
msgid "Tasmiṃ kho pana saṅgāme rājā māgadho ajātasattu vedehiputto rājānaṃ pasenadiṃ kosalaṃ parājesi. "
msgstr "And in that battle Ajātasattu defeated Pasenadi, "

#. VAR: sakameva → saṅgāmā (mr)
#. VAR: paccuyyāsi → pāyāsi (bj, pts1) | paccāyāsi (pts2)
msgctxt "sn3.14:1.8"
msgid "Parājito ca rājā pasenadi kosalo sakameva rājadhāniṃ sāvatthiṃ paccuyyāsi. "
msgstr "who withdrew to his own capital at Sāvatthī. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc2
msgctxt "sn3.14:2.1"
msgid "Atha kho sambahulā bhikkhū pubbaṇhasamayaṃ nivāsetvā pattacīvaramādāya sāvatthiṃ piṇḍāya pavisiṃsu. "
msgstr "Then several mendicants robed up in the morning and, taking their bowls and robes, entered Sāvatthī for alms. "

msgctxt "sn3.14:2.2"
msgid "Sāvatthiyaṃ piṇḍāya caritvā pacchābhattaṃ piṇḍapātapaṭikkantā yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkamiṃsu; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdiṃsu. Ekamantaṃ nisinnā kho te bhikkhū bhagavantaṃ etadavocuṃ: "
msgstr "Then, after the meal, when they returned from alms-round, they went up to the Buddha, bowed, sat down to one side, and told him what had happened. Then the Buddha said: "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts2ed1.189, sc3
msgctxt "sn3.14:3.1"
msgid "“Idha, bhante, rājā māgadho ajātasattu vedehiputto caturaṅginiṃ senaṃ sannayhitvā rājānaṃ pasenadiṃ kosalaṃ abbhuyyāsi yena kāsi. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn3.14:3.2"
msgid "Assosi kho, bhante, rājā pasenadi kosalo: "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn3.14:3.3"
msgid "‘rājā kira māgadho ajātasattu vedehiputto caturaṅginiṃ senaṃ sannayhitvā mamaṃ abbhuyyāto yena kāsī’ti. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn3.14:3.4"
msgid "Atha kho, bhante, rājā pasenadi kosalo caturaṅginiṃ senaṃ sannayhitvā rājānaṃ māgadhaṃ ajātasattuṃ vedehiputtaṃ paccuyyāsi yena kāsi. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn3.14:3.5"
msgid "Atha kho, bhante, rājā ca māgadho ajātasattu vedehiputto rājā ca pasenadi kosalo saṅgāmesuṃ. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn3.14:3.6"
msgid "Tasmiṃ kho pana, bhante, saṅgāme rājā māgadho ajātasattu vedehiputto rājānaṃ pasenadiṃ kosalaṃ parājesi. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn3.14:3.7"
msgid "Parājito ca, bhante, rājā pasenadi kosalo sakameva rājadhāniṃ sāvatthiṃ paccuyyāsī”ti. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc4
msgctxt "sn3.14:4.1"
msgid "“Rājā, bhikkhave, māgadho ajātasattu vedehiputto pāpamitto pāpasahāyo pāpasampavaṅko; "
msgstr "“Mendicants, King Ajātasattu has bad friends, companions, and associates. "

msgctxt "sn3.14:4.2"
msgid "rājā ca kho, bhikkhave, pasenadi kosalo kalyāṇamitto kalyāṇasahāyo kalyāṇasampavaṅko. "
msgstr "But King Pasenadi has good friends, companions, and associates. "

#. VAR: Ajjeva → ajjatañca (bj, pts1) | ajjevaṃ (s1-3, km)
msgctxt "sn3.14:4.3"
msgid "Ajjeva, bhikkhave, rājā pasenadi kosalo imaṃ rattiṃ dukkhaṃ seti parājito”ti. "
msgstr "Yet on this day King Pasenadi will have a bad night’s sleep as one defeated.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn3.14:4.4"
msgid "Idamavoca … pe … "
msgstr "That is what the Buddha said. … "

#. HTML: </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. REF: sc5
msgctxt "sn3.14:5.1"
msgid "“Jayaṃ veraṃ pasavati, "
msgstr "“Victory gives rise to enmity; "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn3.14:5.2"
msgid "dukkhaṃ seti parājito; "
msgstr "the defeated sleep badly. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn3.14:5.3"
msgid "Upasanto sukhaṃ seti, "
msgstr "The peaceful sleep well, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn3.14:5.4"
msgid "hitvā jayaparājayan”ti. "
msgstr "having left victory and defeat behind.”"

#. HTML: </p></blockquote></article></section></body></html>
